Configuring Time Service

Understanding Linux Time:

Hardware Clock = Clock that resides on main card of a system
Real-time Clock = Same as hardware clock
System Time = Time maintained by operating system
UTC = Universal Time Coordinated. Worldwide standard time

NTP:

/etc/chrony.conf = Configuration file for NTP

Commands:

timedatectl set-ntp 1  = Turns on NTP
date = Show current system time
hwclock = Shows hardware clock
timedatectl status = Show current time settings
timedatectl set-time TIME = Set current time
timedatectl set-timezone ZONE = Set current time zone.
timedatectl list-timezone
